From 2e334922edcfb6d237b15ac4fa5644270fb4ef92 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 11:49:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cli: env-driven host/port; insecure TLS for self-signed;
 non-interactive dev login
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

These changes let the CLI talk to a locally-running Caspar node and
dispatch programs/deploy/signal flows correctly against the server.

* Decillion ctor: honour DECILLION_HOST / DECILLION_PORT / DECILLION_PROTO
  env vars so the CLI can target any node, not just api.decillionai.com.
* connectoToTlsServer: when DECILLION_INSECURE=1, drop the strict cert
  check for both the tcp and ws transports — required for local nodes
  using a self-signed cert.
* runNonInteractive: short-circuit `help` and `clear` before opening the
  socket so users can read docs without a network connection.
* loginDev command + Decillion.loginDev: skips the auth0 browser round
  trip and submits the raw email as the emailToken. Works against caspar
  nodes running with Firebase disabled (the server's dev-mode treats the
  token as the email).
* programs.deploy: server's DeployInput expects
  {machineId, entityId, entityType, payload, downloadable, metadata},
  not the legacy {machineId, byteCode, runtime, metadata}. Map the CLI
  args onto the canonical shape (byteCode -> payload, runtime ->
  entityType, metadata.entity/entityId -> entityId, default "main").
* creatures.signal: forward programId and entityId at the top level so
  the server's Signal action can route the packet to the program's VM
  listener (Vmm.Assign registers listeners under the programId). Without
  these the signal stops at the creature, where no VM listener exists.
* Added `ws` (and @types/ws) to runtime dependencies — index.ts was
  importing it but the package was missing.
